The paper proposes a deep learning framework for robotic manipulation, which involves computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category. The paper also focuses on video understanding and sequential modeling, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new deep learning architecture, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
